Ken Dunn wrote:
> The engine started up immediately.  Woohoo!  The timing was WAY off
> after installing the Pertonix.  I was surprised by that.  I only

I would expect that.  It's not necessarily in the same phase orientation 
as the points.  No biggie, though, as you can just rotate the 
distributor and readjust the timing.

> I'm back to 20w-50 now.  It still idles fast.  Is there anything else
> I can check?

I'd try taking off the hose that goes to the aux air regulator and plug 
off both openings with corks.  If your idle drops, then your regulator 
isn't closing all the way.

